BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event-40@atlantahamradio.org
DTSTAMP:20260708T181140Z
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260620T053000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260620T100000
SUMMARY:Chattahoochee Nature Center Possum Trot 10K
LOCATION:Chattahoochee Nature Center\, 9135 Willeo Road\, Roswell\, GA
DESCRIPTION:The 48th Annual Possum Trot 10K is a Peachtree Road Race qualif
 ier benefiting the Chattahoochee Nature Center's environmental education an
 d wildlife rehabilitation programs. Last year drew more than 800 runners. H
 am radio operators provide the only effective means of communicating field 
 conditions back to race organizers and emergency personnel — stationed at
  the starting line\, mile markers\, turnarounds\, and course waypoints. Ope
 rators watch for and report injured or in-distress runners\, vehicles on th
 e closed course\, and other safety issues\, and coordinate the start of mil
 e-marker race timers.
URL:https://arc.groups.io/g/main/message/14633?p=%2C%2C%2C20%2C0%2C0%2C0%3A
 %3A%2C%2C%2C0%2C0%2C0%2C119591891
CATEGORIES:Public Service
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
